== Effect ==

The human attribute is used to determine the following things:
*Whether [[eat]]ing a monster is [[cannibalism]] for a [[human (starting race)|human player]]{{refsrc|eat.c|442}}.
*Whether a [[sacrifice]] is of your own race for a human player{{refsrc|pray.c|1167}}.
*Whether killing a monster is [[murder]]{{refsrc|mon.c|1855}}. Killing humans (and only humans) generated [[peaceful]] is murder, no matter what your starting race.
*The outcome of an attempt to [[tame]] a monster - human monsters cannot be tamed{{refsrc|dog.c|803}}.
*The monster a randomly generated [[figurine]] is for.{{refsrc|mkobj.c|507}} Figurines of human monsters are very rarely generated.
*What to give when [[wish]]ing for a figurine - wishing for a human monster gives a random figurine{{refsrc|objnam.c|2567}}.
*What to give when wishing for the [[corpse]]s of [[quest guardian]]s{{refsrc|objnam.c|2560}}
*What responses to use when [[chat]]ting with other [[role]]s' quest guardians{{refsrc|sounds.c|439}} (possibly created by [[reverse genocide]] or found in [[bones]]).
*Whether a new form is appropriate when a monster is [[polymorphing]] {{refsrc|mon.c|2408}}
*Whether monsters respect [[Elbereth]] or a [[scroll of scare monster]] when you are not standing on it - humans do not.{{refsrc|monmove.c|899}} As {{white|@}} do not respect Elbereth at all, this applies to monsters of other classes with the human attribute, only - currently, this means {{white|K}} [[Keystone Kop]]s.
*Whether to adjust your [[alignment record]] when a monster is [[genocide]]d.{{refsrc|read.c|1636}} Genociding human monsters reduces the alignment record of [[lawful]] adventurers, and increases that of chaotic ones.
*How [[shopkeeper]]s address you{{refsrc|shk.c|2275}} (cosmetic only).
*Whether a [[werecreature]] is in human or animal form{{refsrc|were.c|16}}.

